Title: Single-Path APIs (No Multi-Branch Constructors)

Objective
- Eliminate ambiguous API entry points and constructor overload branches.
- Make intent explicit and code generation consistent.

Hard Rules
1) **Single options object** (no positional params)
   - ✅ `new Thing({ id, x, y })` ❌ `new Thing(id, x, y)`

2) **No method overloads** → one signature with options + defaults

3) **No boolean flags** → explicit keys: `mode: "attack" | "chase"`

4) **No duplicate flows** → centralize logic, call everywhere
   - ✅ `entity.die()` ❌ `killEntity() { entity.die() }` (unless adds value)

5) **Explicit names** → `maxLinearSpeed` not magic numbers

6) **Explicit sync** → document server-only vs synced fields

Review Checklist
- [ ] Single signature, options object, defaults
- [ ] No boolean flags, no redundant wrappers
- [ ] Logic centralized, explicit sync
